                                        </div>
                                    </div>

                                    <h3>Key Finding 1: Exacerbated Ozone Health Impacts</h3>
                                    <p>
                                        <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Changes in average weather conditions that persist over multiple decades or longer. Climate change encompasses both increases and decreases in temperature, as well as shifts in precipitation, changing risk of certain types of severe weather events, and changes to other features of the climate system.

                                        ">Climate change</lex> will make it harder for any given regulatory approach to reduce ground-level <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            A colorless gas consisting of three atoms of oxygen, readily reacting with many other substances. Ozone in the upper atmosphere protects the Earth from harmful levels of ultraviolet radiation from the Sun. In the lower atmosphere ozone is an air pollutant with harmful effects on human health.

                                        ">ozone</lex> pollution in the future as <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Referring to the atmosphere and its phenomena, particularly weather and weather forecasting.

                                        ">meteorological</lex> conditions become increasingly conducive to forming ozone over most of the United States <a class="confidence" data-div="#likely-confidence-div" data-toggle="qtip" title="Likelihood &amp; Confidence">[Likely, High Confidence]</a>. Unless offset by additional <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            The release of climate-altering gases and particles into the atmosphere from human and natural sources.

                                        ">emissions</lex> reductions, these climate-driven increases in ozone will cause premature deaths, hospital visits, lost school days, and <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Occurring over a short period of time (as opposed to chronic).

                                        ">acute</lex> <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Related to the system of organs and tissue the body uses for breathing, including the airways, the lungs and linked blood vessels, and the muscles that enable breathing.

                                        ">respiratory</lex> symptoms <a class="confidence" data-div="#likely-confidence-div" data-toggle="qtip" title="Likelihood &amp; Confidence">[Likely, High Confidence]</a>.
                                    </p>

                                    <div class="supporting-evidence"><a href="report/usgcrp-climate-human-health-assessment-2016/chapter/air-quality-impacts/finding/exacerbated-ozone-health-impacts" class="traceable_account_a qtip-top" title="Supporting Evidence">Supporting Evidence</a></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div id="finding-43" data-ohash="finding-43" class="owl-carousel-item container">
                                <div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10">
                                    <div class="icon-share pull-right">
                                        <a href="#" class="share qtip-bottom" title="Share"></a>

                                        <div class="social-icons">
                                            <a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://health2016.globalchange.gov/facebook/executive-summary?anchor=finding-43" class="social-icon facebook-icon" target="_blank"></a>
                                            <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http://bit.ly/2aQOk0b" class="social-icon twitter-icon" target="_blank"></a>
                                            <a href="#" class="social-icon link-icon"></a>
                                            <div class="link-content"><input type="text" value="executive-summary#finding-43"></div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>

                                    <h3>Key Finding 2: Increased Health Impacts from Wildfires</h3>
                                    <p>
                                        Wildfires emit fine particles and <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            A colorless gas consisting of three atoms of oxygen, readily reacting with many other substances. Ozone in the upper atmosphere protects the Earth from harmful levels of ultraviolet radiation from the Sun. In the lower atmosphere ozone is an air pollutant with harmful effects on human health.

                                        ">ozone</lex> precursors that in turn increase the <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Risks are threats to life, health and safety, the environment, economic well-being, and other things of value. Risks are often evaluated in terms of how likely they are to occur (probability) and the damages that would result if they did happen (consequences).

                                        ">risk</lex> of premature death and adverse <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Occurring over a long period of time (as opposed to acute).

                                        ">chronic</lex> and <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Occurring over a short period of time (as opposed to chronic).

                                        ">acute</lex> <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Referring to the heart and blood vessels. Cardiovascular disease (CVD) includes all diseases and conditions of the cardiovascular system.

                                        ">cardiovascular</lex> and <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Related to the system of organs and tissue the body uses for breathing, including the airways, the lungs and linked blood vessels, and the muscles that enable breathing.

                                        ">respiratory</lex> <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            A state of physical, mental and social well-being, and not just the absence of disease.

                                        ">health</lex> outcomes <a class="confidence" data-div="#likely-confidence-div" data-toggle="qtip" title="Likelihood &amp; Confidence">[Likely, High Confidence]</a>. <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Changes in average weather conditions that persist over multiple decades or longer. Climate change encompasses both increases and decreases in temperature, as well as shifts in precipitation, changing risk of certain types of severe weather events, and changes to other features of the climate system.

                                        ">Climate change</lex> is projected to increase the number and severity of naturally occurring wildfires in parts of the United States, increasing <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            The release of climate-altering gases and particles into the atmosphere from human and natural sources.

                                        ">emissions</lex> of <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            Tiny airborne pieces of solid or liquid matter such as soot, dust, fumes, mists, aerosols, haze, and smoke.

                                        ">particulate matter</lex> and ozone precursors and resulting in additional adverse health outcomes <a class="confidence" data-div="#likely-confidence-div" data-toggle="qtip" title="Likelihood &amp; Confidence">[Likely, High Confidence]</a>.
                                    </p>

                                    <div class="supporting-evidence"><a href="report/usgcrp-climate-human-health-assessment-2016/chapter/air-quality-impacts/finding/increased-health-impacts-from-wildfires" class="traceable_account_a qtip-top" title="Supporting Evidence">Supporting Evidence</a></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div id="finding-44" data-ohash="finding-44" class="owl-carousel-item container">
                                <div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10">
                                    <div class="icon-share pull-right">
                                        <a href="#" class="share qtip-bottom" title="Share"></a>

                                        <div class="social-icons">
                                            <a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://health2016.globalchange.gov/facebook/executive-summary?anchor=finding-44" class="social-icon facebook-icon" target="_blank"></a>
                                            <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http://bit.ly/2aDqf9D" class="social-icon twitter-icon" target="_blank"></a>
                                            <a href="#" class="social-icon link-icon"></a>
                                            <div class="link-content"><input type="text" value="executive-summary#finding-44"></div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <h3>Key Finding 3: Worsened Allergy and Asthma Conditions</h3>
                                    <p>
                                        Changes in <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            The long-term statistical average of weather. Climate typically refers to the mean and variability of relevant weather variables, such as temperature, precipitation, and wind, over long time scales (30 years or more).

                                        ">climate</lex>, specifically rising temperatures, altered precipitation patterns, and increasing concentrations of atmospheric <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            A colorless, odorless, greenhouse gas produced by combustion, respiration, and organic decomposition.

                                        ">carbon dioxide</lex>, are expected to contribute to increasing levels of some airborne allergens and associated increases in <lex class="lexicon-term" title="
                                            A chronic respiratory disease or condition characterized by recurrent breathing problems.

                                        ">asthma</lex> episodes and other allergic illnesses <a class="confidence" data-div="#likely-confidence-div" data-toggle="qtip" title="Likelihood &amp; Confidence">[High Confidence]</a>.
                                    </p>
                                    <div class="supporting-evidence"><a href="report/usgcrp-climate-human-health-assessment-2016/chapter/air-quality-impacts/finding/worsened-allergy-asthma-conditions" class="traceable_account_a qtip-top" title="Supporting Evidence">Supporting Evidence</a></div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
